<br />
<br />I did some googling about the 7805, and using it seems like I'd need to run at least 7V through it for it to work properly, and it'll increase power consumption by around 20-25%, which isn't very helpful at all when using batteries.  It was working perfectly with 4xAAs, and I had it wired up so it would use the original power switch.
<br />
<br />This is kinda OT, but if I have the tip polarity set right, can I use a plain 9VDC adapter inplace of the original 9VAC the NES used?</div>

