				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yes, you can use either polarity DC, or AC.
<br />Just make sure that you use at least 9VDC 500mA.
<br />The bridge rectifier knocks off .6V which drops your 9V down to 8.3, barely 3V above the regulator. Most 5V regulators need at least 7V of DC, with the ripple riding above the 7V (or else you get drop out).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

